About
-----
Simple Hemera speech recognition tools allowing to create models.
Currently it only supports French language.

Full documentation
------------------
You should prefer online documentation: https://gitlab.com/bertrand-benoit/hemerais/wikis

Quick Start
-----------
You need following tools:
 - srilm: language modeling toolkit (See http://www.speech.sri.com/projects/srilm)
 - lia_phon: phonetization tool (French) from LIA labs (See http://lia.univ-avignon.fr/fileadmin/documents/Users/Intranet/chercheurs/bechet/download_fred.html)
 - sphinx3: speech recognition toolkit (See http://cmusphinx.sourceforge.net)

You must install them under the bin/ sub-directory of this project, or create symbolic link to root directory of each installation.
The createModels.sh script will check for these tools availability.

Installation
------------
See online documentation: https://gitlab.com/bertrand-benoit/hemerais/wikis/Third-party%3ASpeechRecognition%3AModels%3Acreate
